<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An illegal alien attempting to cross Interstate 5 in San Ysidro was struck and 
killed Monday night by a hit-and-run driver, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Cornelio Carrasco Carbajal, 32, of Mexico, died at 8:45 p.m. on a stretch of 
I-5 just south of Via de San Ysidro, according to deputy coroner Max Murphy. 
</P>
<P>
Carbajal is the second alien this month, and the sixteenth since Jan. 1, to die 
while crossing border-area freeways on foot, according to CHP officer Larry 
Urban. "That half-mile stretch in San Ysidro accounts for almost all such 
incidents," Urban said. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, 28 pedestrians, most of them aliens illegally entering the United 
States from Mexico, were killed on the freeways near the border, Urban said. 
</P>
<P>
Latino activists have long blamed the Border Patrol practice of chasing aliens 
toward the freeways for boosting the death toll. But Border Patrol officials 
have denied they use that tactic. 
</P>
<P>
Urban said that the Border Patrol has attempted to corner aliens near the 
freeways in the past, but said the practice was discontinued in January. That 
change, along with improved lighting in the area and signs alerting motorists 
of possible pedestrians, lowered the accident rate this year, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
