<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESTROGEN RISK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for your excellent coverage on the increased risk of breast cancer 
with estrogen (Aug. 2). The study in the New England Journal of Medicine on 
which you based your report is one of several that suggest this association. 
Fortunately, newer therapies are being developed that in the future will avoid 
the risk of cancer and will prevent osteoporosis. UCLA is conducting a study 
using a nasal spray medication called calcitonin that prevents osteoporosis and 
has none of the side effects of estrogen. 
</P>
<P>
Hopefully in the future women will be protected against osteoporosis without 
incurring other risks. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. MARIA GREENWALD 
</P>
<P>
Research Associate 
</P>
