<HEADLINE>
<P>
VON HAYES' 3 HOME RUNS LEAD PHILLIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Von Hayes was the whole show Tuesday night at San Francisco as the Philadelphia 
Phillies handed the slumping Giants a 6-1 defeat. 
</P>
<P>
Hayes, benched last week for lack of hitting, hit three home runs and drove in 
all the runs as the Phillies handed the Giants their fourth loss in five games. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first three-homer game for Hayes, who has 21 home runs this season. 
</P>
<P>
Hayes also had two doubles in a 9-1 victory over the Giants Monday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
