<TEXT>
<P>
World record-holder Sebastian Coe ran his fastest 800-meter race since 1985 at 
an international track meet in Bern, Switzerland and Renaldo Nehemiah, who lost 
his world record in the 110-meters hurdles two weeks ago, snapped back with his 
best time in eight years. 
</P>
<P>
Coe, 32, expected to retire after this season, recorded the third-best time in 
the world this season at 1 minute 43.38 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Nehemiah, 30, held off a finish-line challenge from fellow American Tonie 
Campbell to win in 13.20 seconds. Campbell was clocked at 13.27. 
</P>
