<P>
The World Tourism Organization voted to shelve the issue of Palestinian 
membership until 1991. Delegates to the organization's general assembly in 
Paris approved by a 40-34 vote a U.S. motion to postpone any decision on the 
issue. Other members of the 107-member organization were either absent or 
abstained. There was no immediate reaction from Palestine Liberation 
Organization officials. Since the PLO declared a state of Palestine last 
November, publicly renouncing terrorism and recognizing Israel, it has tried to 
