</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KKR Partners Sued: A founder of Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co. sued his 
former partners, claiming that they enriched themselves at his expense. In a 
23-page complaint filed in New York Supreme Court, the state's trial-level 
court, Jerome Kohlberg Jr. alleges that Henry R. Kravis and George R. Roberts 
sharply cut his stake in several companies they had acquired jointly through 
the New York firm. "We believe he is wrong both as to the facts and his 
interpretation of the agreement between us, and we fully expect to prevail in 
court," a spokesman for Kravis and Roberts said. Kohlberg, 64, resigned in 1987 
from the firm he helped found in 1976, citing philosophical differences. He 
remained a limited partner, enabling him to continue as an investor in KKR 
deals. 
