<HEADLINE>
<P>
INDIA BUS BLAST KILLS 12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW DELHI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tribal militants Tuesday detonated a bomb hidden in a bus in northeast India, 
killing at least 12 passengers, a day after tribal leaders agreed to suspend 
the campaign of separatist violence, news reports said. The United News of 
India said the bomb exploded on a state-owned bus in the state of Assam, where 
militants from the Bodo tribes have been fighting for their own state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
