<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marketer of Car Coolant Plans Recycling: Lexington, Ky.-based IG-LO Products, 
maker of a coolant for car air conditioners that is linked to the depletion of 
the Earth's protective ozone layer, announced a recycling and consumer 
education program. Recycling units are to be established at service centers by 
mid-1990 to capture escaped particles of the CFC-12 coolant, known as Freon, 
and allow them to be reused. The chemical breakup of CFC-12 and other 
chlorofluorocarbons -- or CFCs -- in the upper atmosphere has been linked to 
the depletion of the Earth's protective ozone layer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
