<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
HEFNER, NEW WIFE EXPECTING IN APRIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Playboy founder Hugh Hefner, 63, who ended 30 years of bachelorhood last month 
to marry model Kimberley Conrad, will become a father again in April, a Playboy 
spokesman said today. 
</P>
<P>
"For those who wondered how we spent our honeymoon, the answer will be in 
April," the spokesman, Bill Farley, quoted Hefner as telling friends. 
</P>
<P>
Hefner, who for years preached that marriage kills romance, married 26-year-old 
Conrad, a magazine Playmate of the Year, in front of a wishing well at Playboy 
Mansion West on July 1. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second marriage for Hefner, one of the world's best-known bachelors. 
He has two children by his first marriage -- Christie, president of Playboy 
Enterprises, and David. Hefner's first marriage, to Mildred Williams, ended in 
divorce in 1959. 
</P>
</TEXT>
