<P>
An American Airlines MD-80 jet made an emergency landing at an airport today 
after one of its three hydraulic systems failed, an airline spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Flight 891, carrying 66 passengers and a crew of six from Oklahoma City to 
Dallas, returned to Will Rogers World Airport 11 minutes after taking off, said 
American spokesman Jim Brown. He said that even the loss of all three of the 
hydraulic systems would not result in the pilot losing control of the airplane 
as happened with a DC-10 that crashed at Sioux City, Iowa. Brown said a cable 
system would pilot the aircraft in the event of complete hydraulic failure. 
