<P>
AMERICANS HOT IN ITALY HOOP DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROSETO DEGLI ABRUZZI, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Danny Ferry and Brian Shaw, the newly acquired American basketball stars of 
Messaggero Roma, combined for more than half their team's points in a 
tournament game Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Ferry scored 30 points and Shaw added 23 as Messaggero trounced second-division 
Penapesca Montecatini 104-80 in the opening round of the Lido delle Rose 
tournament. It was the first tournament game in Italy for Ferry, the Duke 
All-American who spurned the Clippers, and Shaw, formerly of the Boston 
Celtics. 
</P>
<P>
The victory gave Messaggero a berth in the tournament finals against Arimo 
Bologna, whose lineup includes Americans Chris McNealy and Dave Feitl. Feitl 
and McNealy scored 21 and 15 points, respectively, in Arimo's 94-82 victory 
over Rangers Varese. 
</P>
</TEXT>
