SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japanese Prime Minister Toshiki Kaifu arrived in the United States today to 
"nurture" U.S.-Japan ties and work on global problems with President Bush. 
</P>
<P>
Kaifu, 58, arrived about 10:30 a.m. aboard a chartered Japan Air Lines plane, 
accompanied by his wife, Sachiyo, and six members of Parliament on the first 
stop in a 12-day tour of the United States, Mexico and Canada. 
