<HEADLINE>
<P>
LENDL, GRAF EASILY MOVE UP A ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top seeds Ivan Lendl and Steffi Graf had no trouble advancing today at the U.S. 
Open. 
</P>
<P>
Lendl finished off Diego Perez 6-1, 7-6 (7-1), 6-4 in a first-round match that 
began Tuesday and was suspended by rain. Graf needed all of 44 minutes to blitz 
Nathalie Herreman of France 6-1, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
"I feel that if I play well, I can beat anyone," said Lendl, a finalist here 
the last seven years and a three-time Open champion. "If I don't play well, the 
very next match may be the last." 
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Zina Garrison of the United States beat unseeded countrywoman Gigi 
Fernandez 7-5, 6-4, and 16th seed Hana Mandlikova of Australia defeated Laura 
Golarsa of Italy 7-6 (7-0), 0-6, 6-1 in second-round play. 
</P>
<P>
Also in the second round, Nathalie Tauziat of France beat Kathy Rinaldi of the 
United States 6-2, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
In continuing first-round play, 11th-seeded Jana Novotna of Czechoslovakia 
defeated Meredith McGrath of the United States 7-5, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Among non-seeded players, Jill Hetherington of Canada beat Sandra Cecchini of 
Italy 6-0, 6-3; Rosalyn Fairbank of South Africa beat Peanut Harper of the 
United States 6-3, 6-4; Terry Phelps of the United States defeated Judith 
Wiesner of Austria 2-6, 6-2, 6-4, and Susan Sloane of the United States beat 
Laura Garrone of Italy 6-2, 7-5. 
</P>
<P>
In the second round of men's singles today, No. 2 seed Boris Becker of West 
Germany beat Derrick Rostagno of the United States 1-6, 6-7 (1-7), 6-3, 7-6 
(8-6), 6-3 and Yannick Noah of France beat Todd Witsken of the United States 
6-2, 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Steffi Graf's hair flies as she swings a racket at the U.S. Open. 
Associated Press 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
